1
00:00:01,860 --> 00:00:04,710
Episode 13

2
00:00:14,910 --> 00:00:18,640
II think I like you, Yun.

3
00:00:20,730 --> 00:00:25,170
I like you, Yun.

4
00:00:26,860 --> 00:00:31,940
That's a little... complicated though.

5
00:00:33,370 --> 00:00:36,300
Complicated?

6
00:00:36,300 --> 00:00:42,530
It will be difficult for you and me to have a relationship.

7
00:00:42,530 --> 00:00:47,500
Difficult? Why?

8
00:00:47,500 --> 00:00:56,010
When Ian died, there was another injury on his body, which wasn't from the car crash.

9
00:00:56,010 --> 00:01:03,410
A knife wound. The person who killed him could've been you.

10
00:01:09,910 --> 00:01:17,670
You might not remember, but the one my brother loved was you.

11
00:01:56,050 --> 00:02:03,670
Will you tell me again? I can't understand a word you're saying.

12
00:02:03,670 --> 00:02:09,300
Are you telling me that I might have killed Ian?

13
00:02:14,290 --> 00:02:17,170
Tell me again!

14
00:02:19,700 --> 00:02:25,500
Tell me everything you know. Don't leave anything out.

15
00:02:26,360 --> 00:02:30,710
Was I really Ian Kim's girlfriend?

16
00:02:30,710 --> 00:02:35,070
- From what I know, yes.
- How could you know that? Even I don't know.

17
00:02:35,070 --> 00:02:39,950
Ian told me countless times that there was someone he loved.

18
00:02:39,950 --> 00:02:46,030
- How did you find out that the girl was me?
- If you look at the pictures he took with his girlfriend, anyone would know.

19
00:02:46,030 --> 00:02:52,150
I can't explain with words. I can show you if you want.

20
00:02:52,150 --> 00:02:55,180
Are you saying that your evidence is just a couple of photos?

21
00:02:55,180 --> 00:02:58,940
You said that there are lots of pictures like that.

22
00:02:58,940 --> 00:03:04,780
Alright, let's just say that I really did date him.

23
00:03:04,780 --> 00:03:07,510
Then are you saying that

24
00:03:08,310 --> 00:03:15,300
I killed my boyfriend... killed with a knife?

25
00:03:19,700 --> 00:03:24,390
Why are you saying this to me? You can just reject me if you don't like me!

26
00:03:24,390 --> 00:03:27,300
Just say that you can't date me!

27
00:03:27,300 --> 00:03:30,950
Your purse was found in his car.

28
00:03:30,950 --> 00:03:34,180
That night, you were together.

29
00:03:34,180 --> 00:03:39,690
- What?
- There was a knife wound on his body.

30
00:03:39,690 --> 00:03:45,000
And a knife covered in blood was found where you were passed out.

31
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:48,420
What ... are you saying...?

32
00:03:52,370 --> 00:03:57,910
If that's true, then why wasn't it investigated back then? Why hasn't anyone told me?

33
00:03:57,910 --> 00:04:02,970
Because the case was closed as a hit and run accident. A hit and run.

34
00:04:02,970 --> 00:04:07,570
I personally found the knife at the place you were found.

35
00:04:09,470 --> 00:04:15,350
The day you and I went to the incident scene, you told me. Remember?

36
00:04:15,350 --> 00:04:19,610
You told me that his girlfriend was alive and well.

37
00:04:19,610 --> 00:04:23,030
You can go ask her what happened that day.

38
00:04:24,480 --> 00:04:31,390
I came to you because I wanted to find out directly what exactly happened that day.

39
00:05:01,960 --> 00:05:04,620
Then you're saying

40
00:05:06,010 --> 00:05:10,470
that you've always known who I was.

41
00:05:12,040 --> 00:05:18,780
You knew who I was from the start and came to find me.

42
00:05:18,780 --> 00:05:22,880
You looked for me thinking that I murdered your brother.

43
00:05:22,880 --> 00:05:26,380
That I was a murderer.

44
00:05:28,450 --> 00:05:30,760
Right?

45
00:05:35,340 --> 00:05:43,160
I just wanted to find out what happened that day.

46
00:05:43,160 --> 00:05:49,190
I'm sorry... that I can't tell you.

47
00:05:50,400 --> 00:05:54,610
I can't remember anything from that day.

48
00:05:55,670 --> 00:05:58,480
As you probably already know.

49
00:06:03,570 --> 00:06:06,760
I think I like you.

50
00:06:06,760 --> 00:06:12,170
I thought about it last night and this morning too.

51
00:06:13,210 --> 00:06:15,630
I like you.

52
00:06:15,630 --> 00:06:18,860
Can I kiss you?

53
00:06:21,610 --> 00:06:28,580
You knew who I was from the start and came to find me. Right?

54
00:06:28,580 --> 00:06:32,710
You looked for me thinking that I murdered your brother.

55
00:06:32,710 --> 00:06:38,540
That I was a murderer. Right?

56
00:06:47,940 --> 00:06:52,980
I Wanna Hear Your Song

57
00:07:00,860 --> 00:07:04,070
New pianist Kim Ian dies in car accident.

58
00:07:05,600 --> 00:07:08,670
I looked at this man's face all night long,

59
00:07:08,670 --> 00:07:13,870
but I cannot remember or feel anything.

60
00:07:13,870 --> 00:07:17,520
Did I really love this person?

61
00:07:20,530 --> 00:07:23,720
Did I really...

62
00:07:27,500 --> 00:07:31,050
It's so hot this morning.

63
00:07:31,050 --> 00:07:35,720
- You're here?
- Yes.

64
00:07:36,910 --> 00:07:40,140
Why's your face like that? Are you sick?

65
00:07:40,140 --> 00:07:44,130
No, I just couldn't sleep well last night.

66
00:07:44,130 --> 00:07:48,720
Today's the encore* rehearsal, right? I'll pass out the music sheets.
(An extra piece requested by the audience)

67
00:08:27,020 --> 00:08:29,410
Stop!

68
00:08:34,160 --> 00:08:37,230
What are you doing? Why are you playing like this?

69
00:08:37,230 --> 00:08:42,910
I think our sheet was mixed with another part.

70
00:08:48,760 --> 00:08:50,950
The music sheet?

71
00:08:50,950 --> 00:08:55,350
I'm sorry, I think I mixed up the violin parts.

72
00:09:00,430 --> 00:09:06,640
What can you do with this type of mistake? Do none of you check the music sheets before practice?

73
00:09:06,640 --> 00:09:11,170
If just one of you knew beforehand, there would've been no reason to stop the rehearsal.

74
00:09:11,170 --> 00:09:15,200
I'm sorry. It's my fault.

75
00:09:15,200 --> 00:09:19,930
No, it's my fault. I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

76
00:09:21,480 --> 00:09:24,790
Lets take a break. Return the music sheets.

77
00:09:24,790 --> 00:09:28,630
We'll check them and get them out to you again.

78
00:09:32,890 --> 00:09:36,840
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

79
00:09:55,990 --> 00:09:59,570
Since early this morning you've been spaced out.

80
00:10:01,120 --> 00:10:05,730
You've caused a huge mess.

81
00:10:09,780 --> 00:10:13,280
Just look at your face.

82
00:10:13,280 --> 00:10:16,440
What the heck happened to your face?

83
00:10:18,250 --> 00:10:20,480
Did you have a fight with a guy?

84
00:10:20,480 --> 00:10:22,810
No, it's not like that.

85
00:10:22,810 --> 00:10:25,720
Did that punk Jang Yun two-time you?

86
00:10:25,720 --> 00:10:27,170
I said it's not like that.

87
00:10:27,170 --> 00:10:29,660
Then what is it?

88
00:10:30,590 --> 00:10:32,940
I'm frustrated.

89
00:10:33,850 --> 00:10:35,390
I'm sorry.

90
00:10:35,390 --> 00:10:38,360
I'll tell you everything later.

91
00:10:45,250 --> 00:10:51,480
Je Ni, do you know what kind of relationship Kim Ian  and I had?

92
00:10:51,480 --> 00:10:53,360
What are you talking about suddenly?

93
00:10:53,360 --> 00:10:58,870
Did I possibly tell you that we dated or anything like that?

94
00:10:58,870 --> 00:11:01,030
You didn't.

95
00:11:02,230 --> 00:11:05,000
Did you date him without telling me?

96
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:07,370
It's not like that.

97
00:11:08,590 --> 00:11:11,770
Anyway, thank you. I'll see you later.

98
00:11:17,450 --> 00:11:20,350
What's wrong with her?

99
00:11:24,150 --> 00:11:26,760
Your purse was found in his car.

100
00:11:26,760 --> 00:11:29,520
You two were together on that night.

101
00:11:29,520 --> 00:11:36,190
If what Yun said is true, then I wasn't in a taxi when the accident happened

102
00:11:36,190 --> 00:11:38,880
There was a stab wound on Ian's body.

103
00:11:38,880 --> 00:11:43,230
And there was a knife found where you were passed out.

104
00:11:44,110 --> 00:11:48,610
Could the knife that Yun discovered be the knife that I had?

105
00:11:48,610 --> 00:11:52,850
Did I kill Kim Ian... with that knife?

106
00:11:52,850 --> 00:11:55,300
Why would I?

107
00:11:57,710 --> 00:11:59,700
If I really did kill that person...

108
00:11:59,700 --> 00:12:01,260
Hong Yi Yeong.

109
00:12:01,260 --> 00:12:04,620
If I really did kill Kim Ian...

110
00:12:06,860 --> 00:12:10,250
Hong Yi Yeong... Hong Yi Yeong!

111
00:12:11,240 --> 00:12:12,560
Hong Yi Yeong, wait. Talk to me.

112
00:12:12,560 --> 00:12:15,850
Please. Can you please just leave me alone?

113
00:12:15,850 --> 00:12:17,850
I really don't want to talk to you right now.

114
00:12:17,850 --> 00:12:20,310
Even if you don't want to, you have to. It's what you should do.

115
00:12:20,310 --> 00:12:23,190
I don't know anything. I told you that I don't remember!

116
00:12:23,190 --> 00:12:24,400
Someone died.

117
00:12:24,400 --> 00:12:26,910
A person is dead.  His bones were broken and his organs were smashed—

118
00:12:26,910 --> 00:12:29,390
Please just stop it!

119
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:41,510
Alright, Hong Yi Yeong.
Listen to me. Alright.

120
00:12:41,510 --> 00:12:43,560
I'm not being like this because I want to.

121
00:12:43,560 --> 00:12:49,170
One year ago, on that day, Ian died and you survived.

122
00:12:49,170 --> 00:12:54,020
The one who survives has a responsibility. That goes for for you and for me as well.

123
00:12:56,290 --> 00:13:00,640
I know you don't want to, but remember.

124
00:13:00,640 --> 00:13:05,370
You are the only person who can remember that day. Please.

125
00:13:06,980 --> 00:13:08,860
Please, I beg you.

126
00:13:15,130 --> 00:13:17,580
Then what am I supposed to do?

127
00:13:17,580 --> 00:13:20,670
What if I really did kill Ian?

128
00:13:20,670 --> 00:13:23,120
How can I go on living?

129
00:13:23,120 --> 00:13:26,760
What happens to me doesn't matter for you, does it?

130
00:13:26,760 --> 00:13:29,830
Even if I disappeared, it would mean nothing to you, right?

131
00:13:32,100 --> 00:13:35,800
Because our moments together were all a lie.

132
00:13:36,640 --> 00:13:40,620
Because I may be the disgusting woman who killed your brother.

133
00:13:41,730 --> 00:13:45,040
I wonder what you thought every time you saw me.

134
00:13:46,690 --> 00:13:50,520
How horrible and detestable!

135
00:13:51,210 --> 00:13:54,580
It would have been better if you had told me from the start.

136
00:13:55,410 --> 00:13:58,140
Before I started liking you.

137
00:14:00,130 --> 00:14:04,240
Then it wouldn't be as painful as it is now.

138
00:14:06,220 --> 00:14:09,610
I'm sorry, but please give me more time.

139
00:14:37,690 --> 00:14:41,370
What happened? Hong Yi Yeong left in tears.

140
00:14:42,600 --> 00:14:45,770
I'm concerned why you made her cry.

141
00:14:45,770 --> 00:14:48,180
Are you ordinarily concerned about all orchestra member's private lives?

142
00:14:48,180 --> 00:14:52,560
She's my assistant, so it's natural to care about her.

143
00:14:52,560 --> 00:14:55,580
Even more so with the people who interest me.

144
00:15:00,410 --> 00:15:03,330
Can I ask you to make a delivery to my office?

145
00:15:09,830 --> 00:15:11,680
Work hard.

146
00:15:22,910 --> 00:15:27,330
You too, really... why leave the shade? As things are, why are you sitting here?

147
00:15:28,040 --> 00:15:30,170
Conductor.

148
00:15:31,020 --> 00:15:34,390
I'm sorry. The rehearsal was ruined because of me.

149
00:15:34,390 --> 00:15:36,820
I will make sure that it never happens again.

150
00:15:36,820 --> 00:15:40,550
Fortunately there shouldn't be a second occasion.  The concert is right around the corner.

151
00:15:42,880 --> 00:15:44,030
I'm sorry.

152
00:15:44,030 --> 00:15:47,870
Apology accepted. How about you do a part-time job with me this evening?

153
00:15:47,870 --> 00:15:49,020
A part-time job?

154
00:15:49,020 --> 00:15:54,160
I have somewhere I need to go but I just don't have the courage to go by myself.

155
00:16:28,650 --> 00:16:31,170
Maestro Nam

156
00:16:31,200 --> 00:16:37,300
The person you have called is not available. After the beep...

157
00:16:37,300 --> 00:16:39,020
Where are you?

158
00:16:39,020 --> 00:16:41,450
I hate playing hide-and-seek.

159
00:16:41,450 --> 00:16:47,250
Don't keep making me beg. Don't leave me to my own devices.

160
00:16:47,250 --> 00:16:51,390
Because even I don't know what I will do.

161
00:16:53,840 --> 00:16:56,910
Seaweed Soup Restaurant

162
00:17:02,500 --> 00:17:07,200
Ms. Bok Bun, I'm here.

163
00:17:10,210 --> 00:17:13,840
My god, you jook*-eating jerk!
(congee, East Asian rice porridge)

164
00:17:13,840 --> 00:17:16,660
Why, I was hunting for you and now

165
00:17:16,660 --> 00:17:19,550
you dare show your mug here?

166
00:17:19,550 --> 00:17:22,380
Go. Get out of here!

167
00:17:22,380 --> 00:17:24,240
Hurry up and get out!

168
00:17:24,240 --> 00:17:26,080
Why do you get mad over nothing?

169
00:17:26,080 --> 00:17:28,590
Anyway, you're a pro at playing hard to get.

170
00:17:28,600 --> 00:17:31,800
Dirty dog, stop it right now.

171
00:17:31,800 --> 00:17:34,980
You lying punk!

172
00:17:36,400 --> 00:17:41,050
I have a business to run. Go home and wait or don't.

173
00:17:43,440 --> 00:17:46,070
Who is she?

174
00:17:46,070 --> 00:17:49,430
My goddess, my grandma.

175
00:17:57,250 --> 00:18:02,150
I didn't know that this was your hometown. Until what age did you stay here?

176
00:18:02,150 --> 00:18:05,170
Until I was sixteen. After that, I moved to Seoul.

177
00:18:05,170 --> 00:18:10,680
I'll warn you,  because she is so stubborn,  she has lived alone since then.

178
00:18:10,680 --> 00:18:15,560
My Bok Bun worked so hard every day that she couldn't stand up straight, rolling and frying noodles for money

179
00:18:15,560 --> 00:18:18,370
So that she barely survived.

180
00:18:19,670 --> 00:18:21,940
She really is a goddess.

181
00:18:25,160 --> 00:18:26,280
Aigoo!

182
00:18:26,300 --> 00:18:30,200
What on earth?

183
00:18:30,940 --> 00:18:35,340
Hello, I wasn't able to introduce myself earlier.

184
00:18:35,340 --> 00:18:41,400
I am the Conductor's assistant. My name is Hong Yi Yeong.

185
00:18:43,990 --> 00:18:47,210
Ass iss?

186
00:18:47,210 --> 00:18:51,560
It's an assistant. An assistant is like a secretary.

187
00:18:51,560 --> 00:18:54,090
Like a go-fer, huh?

188
00:18:54,090 --> 00:18:57,800
Why are you saying some kind of bullshit difficult word?

189
00:18:58,750 --> 00:19:01,830
What are you doing just sitting there? Follow me!

190
00:19:01,830 --> 00:19:04,110
Aren't you supposed to serve the guest?

191
00:19:04,110 --> 00:19:06,490
Alright, I'm coming!

192
00:19:06,490 --> 00:19:08,400
Stay here.

193
00:19:10,700 --> 00:19:12,900
You punk!

194
00:19:12,900 --> 00:19:15,930
Stop that.

195
00:19:15,930 --> 00:19:19,370
Here. It's for you.

196
00:19:19,370 --> 00:19:22,810
Why did you worry about getting anything for me?

197
00:19:22,810 --> 00:19:24,060
It's nothing.

198
00:19:24,060 --> 00:19:26,440
Consider it a reward for meeting with CEO Jang.

199
00:19:26,440 --> 00:19:28,740
Thank you.

200
00:19:30,500 --> 00:19:33,940
He said he liked you.

201
00:19:33,940 --> 00:19:37,390
It's the first time I've heard him praise anyone.

202
00:19:37,390 --> 00:19:39,360
I tried to look pretty.

203
00:19:39,360 --> 00:19:40,970
I'm sure you did well.

204
00:19:40,970 --> 00:19:45,630
I'm sure you did well.  You're kind of friendly to people bringing money when they come.

205
00:19:45,630 --> 00:19:47,150
Guilty as charged.

206
00:19:47,150 --> 00:19:50,330
As soon as his contribution comes in, I'm going to recommend him to the board.

207
00:19:50,330 --> 00:19:52,170
I also need someone on my side.

208
00:19:52,200 --> 00:19:57,500
Kang Myeong Seok would like to get involved in the foundation's work.

209
00:19:58,950 --> 00:20:01,790
I will arrange a lunch with them as soon as possible.

210
00:20:01,790 --> 00:20:03,830
There's that.

211
00:20:03,830 --> 00:20:06,970
Did you make a mistake error while I was away?

212
00:20:06,970 --> 00:20:10,380
Mistake? I did?

213
00:20:11,180 --> 00:20:15,970
You knew. Did you purposely keep it from me or did you just not know?

214
00:20:15,970 --> 00:20:17,010
I didn't know!

215
00:20:17,010 --> 00:20:19,450
Do you possible hold a grudge against me?

216
00:20:19,450 --> 00:20:22,340
At the last board meeting, CEO Go said he wanted to serve for a second term.

217
00:20:22,340 --> 00:20:25,270
No way. Never. I'm disappointed.

218
00:20:25,270 --> 00:20:27,500
I should be the one disappointed.

219
00:20:27,500 --> 00:20:31,470
I want to straighten out your sense of loyalty.

220
00:20:31,470 --> 00:20:35,510
I'm not the only one who knows everything the world knows. Even If I'm a wife for show, we are a couple.

221
00:20:35,510 --> 00:20:36,960
This just isn't right, don't you agree?

222
00:20:36,960 --> 00:20:38,470
I'm sorry. It's my fault.

223
00:20:38,470 --> 00:20:40,290
Why did you even do something to be sorry about and leave it be?

224
00:20:40,290 --> 00:20:43,370
You should have taken care of it before I found out.

225
00:20:46,660 --> 00:20:50,320
First off, get rid of that stupid girl.

226
00:20:50,320 --> 00:20:53,000
I am so humiliated, I can't sleep.

227
00:21:02,730 --> 00:21:05,010
Did you practice a lot?

228
00:21:06,530 --> 00:21:08,880
How far did we go last week?

229
00:21:08,880 --> 00:21:11,020
Shall we start with the second measure?

230
00:21:11,020 --> 00:21:16,330
Hey, Teach. I am changing teacher starting this week.

231
00:21:16,330 --> 00:21:20,400
What are you talking about? No one has contacted me about it.

232
00:21:20,400 --> 00:21:25,050
My mother called Professor Kang privately.

233
00:21:25,050 --> 00:21:29,000
Really? Alright.

234
00:21:29,820 --> 00:21:36,630
I don't know why your mother changed her mind, but she should at least tell me why.

235
00:21:36,630 --> 00:21:39,820
This is... rude, you know.

236
00:21:40,490 --> 00:21:43,340
We have worked together for more than 3 years.

237
00:21:45,780 --> 00:21:50,530
There are a lot of rumors circulating among the mothers at my school recently.

238
00:21:50,530 --> 00:21:53,280
What rumor?

239
00:21:53,280 --> 00:21:58,210
They're saying you bought your Guadagnini by selling your body to a rich man.

240
00:21:59,660 --> 00:22:03,500
My mom said that you are dirty.

241
00:22:13,870 --> 00:22:15,990
Crazy bitch Choi Seo Ju.  I'm not going to lose to that scumbag.

242
00:22:15,990 --> 00:22:19,190
She worried that I would lose compared to that trash?

243
00:22:29,060 --> 00:22:32,190
I don't know. I finally feel that I can live.

244
00:22:32,190 --> 00:22:35,910
I've never seen you eat so much.

245
00:22:35,910 --> 00:22:40,650
I used to eat this when I was young.  My taste was not refined.

246
00:22:40,650 --> 00:22:42,550
Our Bok Bun's hands are the same.   The taste has not changed at all.

247
00:22:42,550 --> 00:22:46,460
You make it sound so easy.

248
00:22:46,460 --> 00:22:50,590
When you're done eating, wash your bowl

249
00:22:50,590 --> 00:22:52,830
and lie down.

250
00:22:52,830 --> 00:22:54,180
Grandma, I'll take it.

251
00:22:54,180 --> 00:22:57,350
Get away. It still feels light to me.

252
00:22:57,350 --> 00:22:59,490
Give it to me. Give it to me!

253
00:22:59,490 --> 00:23:01,670
Aigoo.

254
00:23:01,670 --> 00:23:03,310
Where should I put it?

255
00:23:03,310 --> 00:23:05,750
Just put it here.

256
00:23:08,630 --> 00:23:12,160
You know, there's only one of these which is clean.

257
00:23:12,160 --> 00:23:13,980
Yes Ma'am.

258
00:23:13,980 --> 00:23:15,360
Wait, what?

259
00:23:15,360 --> 00:23:18,210
Why do you look so surprised?

260
00:23:18,210 --> 00:23:21,610
Were you planning to not sleep and just leave?

261
00:23:23,740 --> 00:23:25,700
No but...

262
00:23:25,700 --> 00:23:31,100
It's the first time that kid brought anyone here to stay over.

263
00:23:31,100 --> 00:23:31,890
What?

264
00:23:31,890 --> 00:23:35,130
Are you deaf? Ever since he has lived here,

265
00:23:35,130 --> 00:23:39,540
he has never brought over a single friend.

266
00:23:39,600 --> 00:23:45,300
He would die rather than give up his pride.

267
00:23:45,300 --> 00:23:48,300
Now  he's showing some sense.

268
00:23:51,630 --> 00:23:55,280
I have to find the mosquito net.

269
00:24:09,600 --> 00:24:10,580
What about Grandma?

270
00:24:10,580 --> 00:24:14,230
She said she was going to bed. She just turned off all the lights.

271
00:24:14,230 --> 00:24:18,480
She normally sleeps at 8 because she gets up early in  the morning.

272
00:24:20,310 --> 00:24:24,030
Why? Because you can't go back to Seoul?

273
00:24:24,030 --> 00:24:27,010
I didn't think I was going out today.

274
00:24:27,010 --> 00:24:29,350
Isn't there a rehearsal tomorrow?

275
00:24:29,350 --> 00:24:32,800
I can't be at rehearsal tomorrow because of my seminar. Check your text messages.

276
00:24:32,800 --> 00:24:35,760
Assistant Yang sent out notices.

277
00:24:41,020 --> 00:24:44,690
But... why did you suddenly come here?

278
00:24:44,690 --> 00:24:47,120
Because of you.

279
00:24:47,120 --> 00:24:49,420
You cried, remember?

280
00:24:49,420 --> 00:24:51,610
Because of me?

281
00:24:54,040 --> 00:24:56,180
Why are you surprised?

282
00:24:58,570 --> 00:25:00,800
My grandma sent me a text.

283
00:25:00,800 --> 00:25:04,440
I'm hunting for you. I'm sick, you bastard!

284
00:25:06,160 --> 00:25:08,230
She really is good at texting.

285
00:25:08,230 --> 00:25:10,350
She is better than I am.

286
00:25:10,350 --> 00:25:13,650
Saying she is sick means she's asking "Why aren't you coming?"

287
00:25:13,650 --> 00:25:15,630
She's been badmouthing me all this time.

288
00:25:15,630 --> 00:25:19,880
I haven't been able to come since last summer.

289
00:25:20,480 --> 00:25:22,680
For me, it's a year.

290
00:25:29,220 --> 00:25:31,550
But why were you crying earlier?

291
00:25:31,550 --> 00:25:36,520
I think you and Yun had a fight. Was it a lovers' quarrel?

292
00:25:36,520 --> 00:25:38,300
Please.

293
00:25:38,300 --> 00:25:41,430
Even if you don't want to remember, remember!

294
00:25:42,650 --> 00:25:45,150
There is nobody else but you who can remember that day.

295
00:25:45,150 --> 00:25:47,340
I beg you, please.

296
00:25:52,230 --> 00:25:55,100
I also wish I could.

297
00:25:56,820 --> 00:25:59,740
I have something that's really bothering me.

298
00:25:59,740 --> 00:26:02,360
What is it?

299
00:26:03,880 --> 00:26:06,070
Well...

300
00:26:09,310 --> 00:26:13,090
If you don't want to answer, then you don't have to.

301
00:26:13,090 --> 00:26:16,220
It is nice to have come here today.

302
00:26:16,220 --> 00:26:19,610
To just be without thinking.

303
00:26:19,610 --> 00:26:24,340
You and I both need days like this sometimes.

304
00:26:57,870 --> 00:27:02,460
I thought you were bombing my by texting. What's with 32 messages?

305
00:27:02,460 --> 00:27:05,880
I came to Chuncheon. I can't go today.

306
00:27:43,510 --> 00:27:47,230
Mr. Tone-Deaf

307
00:28:06,390 --> 00:28:08,900
Why aren't you sleeping?

308
00:28:08,900 --> 00:28:13,170
Because of the sound of you catching mosquitoes.

309
00:28:13,170 --> 00:28:14,660
There are so many mosqitoes out here.

310
00:28:14,660 --> 00:28:17,720
Even if I kill one, it's useless.

311
00:28:19,380 --> 00:28:21,940
What are you listening to?

312
00:28:21,940 --> 00:28:23,550
Debussy.

313
00:28:23,550 --> 00:28:27,700
It's been a while. Looking at the moon makes me sentimental.

314
00:28:45,510 --> 00:28:48,320
It's been such a long time since I've listened to this.

315
00:28:48,320 --> 00:28:49,980
Me too.
